Reality TV star, Mercy Eke, has said she had a dream where she was a preacher and winning souls for God. The BBN ‘Pepper Dem Geng’ season 4 winner revealed this via a Snapchat post in which she claimed she had not ingested any alcoholic drink, attended a party or committed any sin. She noted she had been chaste from the beginning of the year and has continued till the eighth day.   TOKE MAKINWA: Somebody’s son must find me in 2022     D’Banj hypes Dubai Soundoff as Afrobeat fans win…     PHOTOS: Davido, 30BG crew on groomsmen duties in Zimbabwe   According to the 28-year-old media personality, ‘outside’ is, however, already beckoning on her but she prays for strength to overcome the desire to return to a sinful life. - Advertisement - “Day 8: No alcohol, no lies, no sin, no party. God, I need more strength to keep going but outside is already calling my name,” Eke wrote.